Description of incident: A filing error in Maryland's federal            court resulted in health insurance information for 226 people - including            42 Social Security numbers - being made available to the public for            more than two weeks. The private information of Washington area residents            was included in requests for warrants to search the doctors' offices            in Suitland, La Plata, Oxon Hill and Falls Church as part of a health            care fraud investigation. The warrants were marked as being sealed and,            therefore, were not supposed to be made public.
